text: The drab moray (Gymnothorax monochrous) is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.Gymnothorax monochrous at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Pieter Bleeker in 1856, and is also commonly known as the brown moray, monochrome moray, monotone moray, or plain moray eel.Common names for Gymnothorax monochrous at www.fishbase.org. ==References== ==External links== * Fishes of Australia : Gymnothorax monochrous drab moray Category:Marine fish of Northern Australia drab moray
